s of social actors and machines, industrial, educational, ethnographic, and other process films stake out diverse ideological positions on the meaning of labor and on a society's level of technological development. In systematically theorizing a genre familiar to anyone with access to a screen, Skvirsky opens up new possibilities for film theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aMotion picturesxHistory. 0aProcess filmsxHistory and criticism. 0aWork in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertArt and Architecture eBook-Package 2020z978311073823008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069631808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2020z9783110704655oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478007074zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478007074423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478007074/original  a978-3-11-069631-8  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070478-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-073823-0  Art and Architecture eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DPKb2020